---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-19";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Terms of use — PDF Tools"
	description="The rules for using pdf.oriz.in."
	canonical="/legal/terms"
>
	<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-blue-50/30 border-b border-gray-200/60">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
			<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">
				<a href="/" class="hover:text-gray-900">PDF Tools</a> /
				<a href="/legal/" class="hover:text-gray-900">Legal</a> / Terms
			</p>
			<h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight mb-2">
				Terms of use
			</h1>
			<p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Last updated: {updated}</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 prose prose-gray max-w-none">
		<p>
			By using pdf.oriz.in or any <code>*.oriz.in</code> site, you agree to these terms.
			They are short on purpose.
		</p>

		<h2>Use the sites lawfully</h2>
		<p>
			Don't try to break the sites, scrape them at abusive rates, or use them
			to harass others. Account takeover, copyright infringement, and any
			activity prohibited under Indian law are forbidden. Don't use these
			tools to process content you don't have the right to process.
		</p>

		<h2>Content is provided as-is</h2>
		<p>
			PDF tools on pdf.oriz.in are provided for information and convenience
			only. They are not professional advice. Verify outputs before relying on
			them, especially for legal or financial documents. See the full
			<a href="/legal/disclaimer/">disclaimer</a>.
		</p>

		<h2>Your content</h2>
		<p>
			Anything you process with our tools stays yours and stays on your device.
			We do not receive a copy of your files — they are processed entirely in
			your browser. Account preferences and settings stay with you.
		</p>

		<h2>Termination</h2>
		<p>
			You can delete your account at any time from the
			<a href="/account/">account page</a>. We can suspend accounts engaged in
			abuse without notice.
		</p>

		<h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
		<p>
			To the maximum extent permitted by law, oriz and its operator are not
			liable for any indirect or consequential damages arising from use of
			the sites. Since processing happens in your browser, we cannot recover
			lost or corrupted files; keep backups of important documents.
		</p>

		<h2>Governing law</h2>
		<p>
			These terms are governed by the laws of India. Disputes will be settled
			in the courts of Bhubaneswar, Odisha.
		</p>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>
